commitResults.messageBody:
Implements a command to create meetings.

Let's,
* update the Logic component to
  - support a command to create meetings
  - parse the arguments to the command to create meetings
  - return a view of the meetings list
* update the Model component to
  - store Meeting objects which represent a meeting
* update the Storage component to
  - save and load meeting details in JSON format
* update the ViewModel component to
  - expose a read-only meetings list to the UI component

Note:
* The UI component is not updated to display the meetings list
* Tests have yet to be (re)written

commitResults.messageTitle: Update and fix bugs related to UG (#276)
commitResults.messageBody:
Update and fix bugs related to UG

Let's fix the following bugs,
* Update name of the .jar file to `teamsync.jar` (#208)
* Update UI screenshot (#209)
* Update example of `person add` to show modules being added (#211)
* Move description about not allowing duplicate teammates / modules to
a note callout box instead (#215)
* Update command group for module commands from `mod` to `module` (#216)
* Update ToC links (#217)
* Remove incorrect description that modules can be edited with `person
edit` (#222) 
* Add warning that the teammate might shift positions in the teammate
view when changing their name (#223)
* Add section on manually editing data (#224)
* Remove troubleshooting on administrator privileges. This is likely not
a common problem and it is not an issue with TeamSync in particular 
(#228)
* Add note on TeamSync not allowing duplicate modules or meetings (#240)
* We will not be adding an explanation regarding #244 (#244)
* Add description of visual elements under Features section (#250)
* Update example of `person add` to show multiple modules being added.
User can infer that multiple tags can be added in a similar manner.
(#252)
* Add explanation to why we allow adding of meetings in the past (#262)
* Add description of how TeamSync defines duplicate persons in the
Glossary (#263)
* Add explanation as to why we only support editing modules through
`module add` and `module delete` (#264)

Let's also,
* Update landing page (not part of UG)
* Update Features section
* Add descriptions and images of the visual elements in our UI
* Update Quick Start to be more guided as our target users might not be
very tech-savvy
* Update examples to be more representative
* Add extended description and screenshots for certain commands
* Update current FAQ to be more understandable and remove wrong
responses / unnecessary questions
* Add other FAQ on why TeamSync functions in a specific way
* Update glossary
* Use color coding when appropriate
* Use internal and external links when appropriate
* Standardize formatting and language
* Various other updates to improve reading experience
